Utterances: hello
Hey! What's up?
what brings you in today
Those idiot cops brought me here. I don't need to be here but the front desk guy said that they have to check me out. Like I'm some sort of book in the history of atlases.
what happened

I was in a parking lot of a grocery store. Apparently it's against the law to run around and look into cars now for your own protection. They wouldn't be laughing if a government agent was indeed waiting in one of them to snap me up. Can't be too careful.
what do you mean government agent

I mean, what do you want to know? I just had a hunch they were in one of those cars, waiting to scoop me up and throw me in solitary. They know I'm enlightened and if my writings get out, boom, their secrets are overthrown. Not that I'm gonna let them stop me.
do you have anxiety

I'm not anxious or paranoid or whatever. I mean, I just have a really really fine-tuned sense of, like, OK, now they're coming for me, the government agents, and I have to be on the look out, 'cause no way am I being snatched up, not a chance.
are you seeing anything
No way. I don't see junk that's not there or anything.
do you use drugs
I guess cocaine is still illegal, right? That's the war on drugs for ya.
how is your sleep
Well, there's not much of it, but I get a couple hours in usually, and I never feel, like, unrested or anything. Recently, I haven't had to sleep for like, four days. It's sick, completely bangin'.
how is your energy
Awesome! I mean, I'm just a high energy kind of guy, a lot of the time. But this week especially I've felt, like, crazy up and up, and I love it. I just love it. I feel like I could lift a horse.
how is your mood
I am 100% letting the good times roll. Couldn't be better.
last time you used drugs
Haven't done coke since about four days ago, I'd say.
existing health problems
What preexisting health issues do you have?.
Sure, some Doc McGillicutty told me I had depression one time, but I got that beat! (Clarified to what preexisting health problems I have.)
how is your mood typically
You've got Option A and Option B. With A, we're talking about a bottomless rat hole. With B, we're talking good vibes that don't disappoint. I'll stick with B, thanks.
how often does  your mood change
I'm not keeping track or anything, but maybe a couple times a year? I don't know. This is a really nice room. I really like this room.
when were you last depressed

I mean . . . I fully got out of it maybe a couple months ago . . . it started a while before that. I dunno. Time isn't really linear, you know? I don't think in terms of, like, oh, this happened, now this'll happen.
what is your depression like

Oh, man. I hope you're not trying to ruin my vibes. Because my vibes are electric right now. I'm fully lit--but yeah, I've been down before. That's not what I'm trying to focus on right now, the depression diagnosis or whatever.
can you tell me about the depression diagnosis

I mean, that doctor was a buffoon, but I get where he was coming from -- I had just tried to kill myself. That doesn't necessarily scream NOT depressed, you know? Like, your eyeballs are your eyeballs. You see what you see.
allergies
Not at all. I'm allergic to bad vibes is all. That stuff is palpable. Like, oh boy, it's pollen season.
how was your depression treated
That quack of a doctor put me on antidepressants. Yeah, sure took a lot of self-interrogation to write stuff on a pad. I mean, my god. No intellect whatsoever.
did the medication work

The antidepressants didn't do diddly squat. Not a squat in sight. Squatless. In fact, those little buggers made things worse, if you can believe it. Can you believe it? I mean, holy hell. Anyway, I just stopped taking them. Some problems have easy solutions. Ask any scientist.
were there side effects
Yeah, the antidepressos did some stuff to me. Whatever. Bullcrap little -- just -- just stupid, stupid stuff. No one needs 'em.
what were the side effects
are you still taking that medication
Do you still take the antidepressants?.
are you still taking that medication (Clarified to Do you still take the antidepressants?.)

Heck no. After a few months on them, I knew they weren't for me. The doc said to talk to him before making any changes, but hey, he didn't talk to me before putting me on them! Hehe. Well, he did, but you know what I mean. (Clarified to if I am still taking antidepressants.)
what other medications do you take
I've only ever taken antidepressants.
can you tell me about the prescription

All I remember is that they didn't work, they made me feel like . . . whatever, they sucked. They were--they were suck pills. That's all I remember. They were suck pills made in Sucksville and I hope they rot in Sucks Hell.
did you try to kill yourself
I really don't want to talk about it. You're being a bummer, honestly. I was in a good mood before we started talking about this.
Im sorry
Thanks a million, but I'm all good, I promise!
have you tried to kill yourself more than once
Just the once . . . and you really don't have to worry about me like that.
did you want to be dead
No, it was because I was really happy and my life was going great. What do you think?
do you still wish you wanted to be dead
Nah, that would be nuts. I've got so much in the works. My life's coming together. Everything's falling into place. Feeling worthless, or whatever, that was only during my depression.
did you think others would like it better if you werent here (No matching questions found.)
did you think other people wanted you dead
I don't really care what people think of me, especially if people aren't hip to my vibes.
did you think others would be better off without you
When I tried to kill myself maybe, I don't know, I don't think about that anymore, but I definitely don't feel that way now. Why would I? Everything's going great.
